WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:06.089
Let's stand together and we're going to read one more time from the book of Philippians, but we're going to read a different passage.

00:06.129 --> 00:06.450
All right.

00:06.830 --> 00:08.953
And so let's turn back to Philippians chapter three.

00:08.993 --> 00:10.555
I told you this morning I preached part one.

00:10.735 --> 00:17.763
I'm going to preach part two now and we're going to have brother Williams is going to sing for us right after I read this passage.

00:18.725 --> 00:21.768
And then we'll get right into the message for tonight.

00:22.229 --> 00:26.514
Philippians chapter three, I read already verses 12, 13, 14.

00:27.170 --> 00:33.579
I'd like to read it this time, verses 15 and 16, if you would, follow with me, verses 15 and 16.

00:35.001 --> 00:38.065
We've already read about pressing toward the mark, reaching forth.

00:38.606 --> 00:48.359
So in verse 15, we read, let us therefore, now can I just tell you, the Christian life was not designed for someone to try to live it on their own.

00:50.222 --> 00:53.426
Paul is not just giving his testimony, he's giving a challenge.

00:54.402 --> 00:57.806
I did not just give to you a testimony of what I'd like to do.

01:00.649 --> 01:02.511
If we don't all get involved, none of it happens.

01:03.873 --> 01:04.834
Let us therefore.

01:06.315 --> 01:07.877
Paul said, I'm striving to get it.

01:07.897 --> 01:13.063
Paul said, I'm reaching forth and you could imagine somebody to fill up by going, wonderful.

01:13.163 --> 01:14.625
Paul's zeal is just wonderful.

01:15.485 --> 01:17.548
But Paul wasn't saying that just for himself.

01:17.688 --> 01:20.051
He was saying, let all of us therefore.

01:21.312 --> 01:23.154
All of us, let us therefore.

01:23.650 --> 01:29.178
Let us therefore, as many as be perfect, be thus minded speaking about being saved.

01:30.159 --> 01:36.388
And if in anything ye be otherwise minded, God shall reveal even this unto you.

01:37.390 --> 01:42.918
Nevertheless, where to we have already attained, let us walk by the same rule.

01:44.160 --> 01:51.250
Let us mind the same thing, verse 17, brethren, be followers together of me,

01:52.098 --> 01:56.585
and mark them which walks so as you have us for an ensemble.

01:56.966 --> 01:57.507
Let us pray.

01:57.967 --> 02:16.617
Father, in these final moments, as we look to this book of Philippians, I pray that you would bring this day together in a grand climax, Lord, in a wonderful time of dedication that we all together would reach forth and that we would see what you can do when many hundreds of people are thirsting, hungry for you.

02:17.138 --> 02:19.141
In Jesus' name I pray, amen.

02:19.181 --> 02:19.922
You may be seated.

02:20.482 --> 02:28.496
This morning we learn from God's word that we want to be a church that is reaching forth, going forth into the new year.

02:29.217 --> 02:32.222
And tonight we stand at the starting line of this new year.

02:33.204 --> 02:36.990
We stand looking ahead, asking God to work and to bless.

02:37.952 --> 02:43.421
Now the Bible speaks about these athletic opportunities in the spiritual realm.

02:43.441 --> 02:46.226
1 Corinthians 9 and 24.

02:46.530 --> 02:50.695
No you not that they which run in a race run all, but one receive at the prize.

02:51.516 --> 02:53.038
So run that you may obtain.

02:53.098 --> 02:58.465
And every man that strived for the mastery is temperate in all things.

02:59.366 --> 03:05.394
Now they do it to obtain a corruptible crown, but we an incorruptible.

03:06.656 --> 03:14.706
In this life we almost decide and determine will I live only for the corruptible things or for the incorruptible.

03:15.778 --> 03:17.500
There's nothing wrong with going to the gym.

03:17.540 --> 03:21.464
There's nothing wrong with having, you know, a muscular body.

03:22.485 --> 03:25.749
But I hate to tell you tonight that's a temporal thing.

03:28.011 --> 03:33.998
Nothing wrong with having something new and something nice, but all the things of this world are corruptible.

03:35.359 --> 03:40.205
But those things that are done for Jesus are incorruptible.

03:40.225 --> 03:45.010
And we're reaching forth this year for the incorruptible things.

03:45.698 --> 04:01.005
The National Football League is buying now for placement and hopefully into the Super Bowl and the college football championship and all of these are worldly pursuits and I want to tell you something tonight that in heaven those things are not exciting.

04:01.025 --> 04:04.652
The angels yawn when it comes to the NFL Super Bowl.

04:07.437 --> 04:10.482
But when one soul is saved, there's rejoicing in heaven.

04:12.322 --> 04:16.287
I propose that we ought to then live our lives with eternity in mind.

04:16.307 --> 04:20.913
We ought to live our lives with what causes rejoicing in heaven.

04:20.993 --> 04:24.638
And I think all of us would agree that the spiritual goals matter more.

04:25.539 --> 04:29.985
What does it profit a man if he gains the whole world and loses his own soul?

04:30.105 --> 04:36.594
And certainly there's an application to salvation in that verse, but also to our spiritual well-being.

04:36.866 --> 04:38.107
What does it profit someone?

04:38.568 --> 04:44.955
If in working all their overtime or if in accomplishing all these goals, they lose their heart for God.

04:44.995 --> 04:51.362
And so we want to reach forth, but we want to reach forth for that which is eternal.

04:51.622 --> 04:52.443
Now how do we do that?

04:53.003 --> 04:56.527
Let me give you a few thoughts as Paul continues this challenge.

04:57.148 --> 05:02.994
First tonight, I believe as a church that we must share a common goal.

05:03.458 --> 05:05.244
that we share a common goal.

05:05.284 --> 05:11.986
Notice in verse 15, the Bible says, let us therefore as many as be perfect be thus minded.

05:12.354 --> 05:17.398
This goal, this challenge about reaching forth, this is for the saved tonight.

05:17.699 --> 05:19.600
This is for those of us that have been born again.

05:19.901 --> 05:22.723
It says as many as B as are perfect.

05:22.763 --> 05:26.326
That word perfect means finished or complete.

05:26.386 --> 05:29.569
And by the way, we are all complete in Jesus Christ.

05:29.629 --> 05:42.340
So he is saying that we together share this common goal, that we are the saved and that our goal then is Christ likenessed Romans 8 and 29 being conformed to the image of the Lord Jesus.

05:42.320 --> 05:49.428
And so this challenge that is being given here in Philippians 3, it's not just the power of positive thinking for unsaved people.

05:49.688 --> 05:56.255
It's not corporate training, but this is something specifically to those that are perfect, to those that are in Christ.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.756
It is for the saved.

05:57.797 --> 06:00.179
We share a common goal as saved people.

06:00.339 --> 06:09.909
All of us need to be reaching forth for the incorruptible crown of Jesus Christ, pressing toward the mark of the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.

06:10.010 --> 06:12.292
This is a challenge to the saved.

06:12.272 --> 06:14.995
tonight, and hopefully that is all of us in this room.

06:15.275 --> 06:17.518
It is also a challenge for the future.

06:17.978 --> 06:24.825
You'll notice the Bible says, let us therefore, and whenever you see the word therefore in the Bible, you look to see what it's there for.

06:24.865 --> 06:26.888
You look to the previous verses.

06:27.408 --> 06:34.856
And he is speaking, of course, of verse 13, forgetting those things which are behind and reaching forth under those things which are before.

06:35.237 --> 06:37.639
And so our common goal is 2020.

06:37.759 --> 06:40.903
Our common goal is that we want to start well.

06:41.123 --> 06:42.244
We want to finish well.

06:42.224 --> 06:46.210
We want to keep Jesus in our hearts and minds all through the year 2020.

06:46.350 --> 06:51.177
Hey, I don't think you're here on a Sunday night because you could care less about 2020.

06:51.838 --> 07:00.210
I think every Christian in this room ought to say tonight and believes in their heart tonight that we would like to be closer to Jesus 12 months from now than we are right now.

07:00.951 --> 07:01.853
It's a common goal.

07:02.514 --> 07:03.936
All of us should desire.

07:04.797 --> 07:10.866
May I say that when memories of the past supersede our vision for the future, then our doom is nigh.

07:11.970 --> 07:15.217
It's one thing to say, I got saved and I was faithful back then.

07:15.277 --> 07:17.502
We've seen a lot of buildings built.

07:17.522 --> 07:18.544
We've seen a lot of lives change.

07:18.785 --> 07:19.807
It's another thing to say.

07:19.907 --> 07:21.070
I'm reaching forth.

07:21.090 --> 07:22.733
I want to see another child saved.

07:22.753 --> 07:25.239
I want to see my child's life touched and changed.

07:25.259 --> 07:30.450
I want to see God work in 2020 like he did in years gone by.

07:30.722 --> 07:47.677
And that's why our ministry path is so important and it really reflects the fact that we're reaching forth because we want our worship to be reaching out for God and engaging for those that would visit our community groups to bring them in to fellowship in the connection groups.

07:47.757 --> 08:00.708
And one of the things I have in my mind as soon as we get the kids city building is to expand and remodel our coffee shop to give more area for relationship and maybe emphasize the retail just a little less in the relationship.

08:00.688 --> 08:02.330
and the fellowship just a little more.

08:02.570 --> 08:10.700
And let this place continue to be a place of rest and fellowship for people who want to know God and encourage each other in the Lord.

08:10.740 --> 08:16.267
And so we move from worship to community to commitment or discipleship and service and outreach.

08:16.307 --> 08:27.520
And all of this says, everything that I've said tonight is that we are a church reaching forth into the future and pressing toward Christ and wanting to know Him and please Him and live for Him.

08:27.580 --> 08:28.882
And I said this this morning,

08:29.378 --> 08:31.601
But I believe we ought to do this with great passion.

08:32.142 --> 08:37.731
Paul the Apostle used this phrase in verse number 14, he said, I press toward the mark.

08:37.751 --> 08:38.612
Would you say that with me?

08:39.073 --> 08:40.435
I press toward the mark.

08:40.455 --> 08:50.691
One more time, I... You say, well, I'm pressing for this amount of weight, and I'm pressing for this promotion, and I'm pressing for this college degree.

08:50.971 --> 08:53.916
But are you pressing to know Jesus Christ?

08:56.240 --> 08:57.842
Is it a passion in your heart?

08:59.170 --> 09:01.573
Say, well, I need to know why that's so important.

09:02.454 --> 09:05.778
As I said this morning, if you know the who, you'll know the why.

09:06.939 --> 09:08.041
Jesus is the who.

09:08.982 --> 09:12.666
And you'll want to know Him more and draw closer to Him.

09:13.427 --> 09:13.708
C.S.

09:13.768 --> 09:17.372
Lewis once wrote, aim at heaven and you will get earth thrown in.

09:17.412 --> 09:19.595
Aim at earth and you'll get neither.

09:20.997 --> 09:24.301
Have a heavenly mindset, pressing toward the mark.

09:25.302 --> 09:28.786
For the believer, we have been made perfect in Jesus Christ

09:29.122 --> 09:35.218
Our salvation is complete, but this passage is not speaking merely about salvation, it's speaking about

09:35.298 --> 09:36.279
maturation.

09:36.599 --> 09:38.521
It's speaking about growth in the Lord.

09:38.821 --> 09:45.507
Wiersby says, Paul is not talking about salvation, but about sanctification, growth, and progress in the Christian line.

09:45.707 --> 09:47.388
He says, I want to continue growing.

09:47.649 --> 09:48.730
I want to know him more.

09:48.970 --> 09:52.153
I'm pressing toward the mark of the prize of the high calling of God.

09:52.393 --> 09:54.455
And what I'm saying is we have a common goal tonight.

09:54.715 --> 10:03.302
And we're all here with a goal of spiritual maturity and knowing Christ in a deeper way and loving Christ and falling in love with Christ in this year.

10:03.522 --> 10:05.284
And that ought to be our prayer no matter

10:05.264 --> 10:10.571
our age or our station in life, that all of us would draw closer to Jesus.

10:10.631 --> 10:11.733
That's our common goal.

10:11.773 --> 10:17.160
But not only do we share a common goal, I want you to notice, secondly, we serve a convicting God.

10:18.742 --> 10:21.245
We serve a convicting God.

10:22.447 --> 10:28.315
Now I want you to see something very interesting, verse 15, it says, let us therefore, as many as be perfect, be thus minded.

10:28.355 --> 10:29.196
Now let's just stop right here.

10:29.617 --> 10:33.682
How many of you would say, pastor, it would be a wonderful thing

10:34.242 --> 10:40.592
If every member of Lancaster Baptist Church, as many as are perfect in Jesus Christ, would be thus minded.

10:40.692 --> 10:45.420
In other words, that every member of this church was passionately pursuing Christ.

10:45.680 --> 10:46.782
That would be revival.

10:47.142 --> 10:49.626
That would be awesome.

10:49.646 --> 10:50.608
How many of you agree with me on that?

10:51.469 --> 10:51.950
Imagine that.

10:52.010 --> 10:53.953
Thousands of people pursuing Christ.

10:53.973 --> 10:56.978
I mean, there are people here tonight checking their phone while I preach.

10:58.338 --> 11:01.002
Sometimes people can't get their heads up to look.

11:01.022 --> 11:01.864
They're disinterested.

11:01.904 --> 11:06.732
Their mind is controlled by social media, rock music, or who knows what else is going on.

11:08.595 --> 11:15.306
So what I'm saying is to get thousands of people with a singular passion for Christ, that might take like a miracle.

11:18.250 --> 11:20.073
But how many of you would say be a wonderful thing indeed?

11:21.876 --> 11:22.898
Now here's the dilemma.

11:24.642 --> 11:27.025
It does not always happen that way.

11:27.206 --> 11:29.068
And you'll notice it because you're human.

11:29.970 --> 11:34.456
You'll notice it because you attend the class and you might see someone's up or down.

11:34.476 --> 11:38.462
By the way, how many have noticed that it's easier to notice someone else's fault than it is your own fault?

11:40.505 --> 11:41.827
Sort of human nature, I guess.

11:42.968 --> 11:44.470
And that's why I want you to see this point.

11:46.093 --> 11:48.236
We serve a convicting God.

11:48.276 --> 11:49.357
Now we share a common goal.

11:49.418 --> 11:51.501
We all want to grow closer to Christ.

11:51.521 --> 11:52.562
That should be our common goal.

11:53.282 --> 11:55.164
But what about when that doesn't happen?

11:56.205 --> 12:03.732
What about when someone doesn't pay attention or someone has gone wayward or somebody isn't living the way you think they should live?

12:03.772 --> 12:05.173
And let me just say this very quickly.

12:06.154 --> 12:10.858
Our greatest concern tonight should not be the other member in the church.

12:12.300 --> 12:14.041
Our greatest concern should be ourself.

12:16.344 --> 12:23.250
Now, as a pastor, I think I have a calling and I have a burden that's broader in the sense of that calling.

12:24.578 --> 12:29.183
But even my number one concern is myself being right with God.

12:31.305 --> 12:42.577
That's why I mentioned earlier about the song, Holy Spirit, you are welcome here and let us lift up and glorify you because there are so many different pressures that can come even on a pastor thinking about this, worrying about this.

12:42.857 --> 12:43.558
What does this one think?

12:43.578 --> 12:44.259
What does that one think?

12:44.279 --> 12:46.902
And sometimes I just have to say, time out, who cares?

12:47.222 --> 12:51.186
All I care about right now is that I am thoroughly right with God myself.

12:53.570 --> 12:57.974
Don't start this year with the idea of everybody ought to be thus minded.

12:57.994 --> 13:04.841
They ought to think the way I think about this verse and that verse and this position and that conviction and be that way.

13:05.021 --> 13:08.625
It would be a beautiful thing if that happens and when we get to heaven, that's what it's going to be.

13:10.146 --> 13:12.248
But until then, I want to remind you of this principle.

13:12.829 --> 13:14.771
We serve a convicting God.

13:16.172 --> 13:17.193
Now, notice what it says here.

13:18.635 --> 13:21.938
If in anything ye be otherwise minded,

13:22.210 --> 13:25.455
God shall reveal even this unto you."

13:26.657 --> 13:31.744
So we see, first of all, that in the context of the local church, sometimes there are airing believers.

13:32.585 --> 13:34.709
They are otherwise minded.

13:34.729 --> 13:39.235
In other words, we may have the mind of Christ on something.

13:39.255 --> 13:43.201
The Scripture might be clear on something, but then there's these people that are otherwise minded.

13:43.922 --> 13:46.126
They're not thinking about the sermon.

13:46.146 --> 13:49.010
They're thinking about something else that they want to do.

13:49.410 --> 13:55.118
And sometimes they'll try to spiritualize, well, you know, I saw a hypocrite in the church, whatever, you'll hear all kinds of excuses.

13:55.178 --> 13:58.923
But the fact is the fruit doesn't signify the growth.

13:59.203 --> 14:07.615
And so suddenly there might be someone that is otherwise minded in this context, meaning they're not mindful of following Christ passionately.

14:07.915 --> 14:10.038
They're more passionate about other stuff.

14:11.020 --> 14:12.161
That sometimes happens.

14:13.543 --> 14:15.666
When that happens, we can have a range of emotions.

14:16.642 --> 14:18.544
You could have the range of a broken heart.

14:18.624 --> 14:20.305
If it's your child, it would break your heart.

14:21.967 --> 14:24.269
You could have the emotion of a burdened heart.

14:26.091 --> 14:28.954
God forbid you could have the emotion of a judgmental heart.

14:30.555 --> 14:34.979
But we have emotions and we have thoughts and sometimes people say things.

14:36.661 --> 14:46.450
What I want you to see here is that when there is an airing believer that there is also an engaging God who is not

14:46.978 --> 14:49.142
up in heaven blind to all of it.

14:49.923 --> 14:50.924
He's very well aware.

14:52.507 --> 14:56.113
Oswald Sanders said, most Bible characters meet with failure and then survived.

14:56.854 --> 15:01.181
Even when the failure was immense, those who rebounded refused to lie in the dust and bemoan their tragedy.

15:01.522 --> 15:04.627
In fact, their failure and repentance led to a greater conception of God's grace.

15:04.647 --> 15:14.162
In other words, our prayer should be that when someone airs, when someone is otherwise minded, we should pray that they will become right with God, that they will be restored into fellowship.

15:14.658 --> 15:19.245
but we should also remember that when there is an airing member, there is an engaging God.

15:19.285 --> 15:23.231
So notice in verse 15, it says, God shall reveal even this unto you.

15:23.271 --> 15:24.032
Let's say that together.

15:24.373 --> 15:27.437
God shall reveal even this unto you.

15:27.898 --> 15:34.107
You see, now this is very important because real conviction comes from God.

15:35.770 --> 15:36.410
Is everybody with me?

15:38.113 --> 15:39.275
Real conviction.

15:39.555 --> 15:41.458
So when someone is airing,

15:41.922 --> 15:44.024
We get burdened, we get worried, we want to say something.

15:44.044 --> 15:47.588
Sometimes people might say something to a friend, we should not do that, it's called gossip.

15:47.969 --> 15:54.536
But when someone is airing, what the Bible says is that God will reveal that to them.

15:54.576 --> 16:05.708
Now, you as a wife can say something to your husband or you as a church member say something to another church member and from time to time it may be your place, maybe you're discipling them, maybe you're married to them, whatever the case might be.

16:05.788 --> 16:11.474
But the fact of the matter is that real true conviction will always come from God.

16:12.866 --> 16:18.634
And normally what we do in a Pharisaical manner, whether we intend it or not, what we give is guilt.

16:18.774 --> 16:22.980
And what guilt does, it builds resentment and it drives people farther away.

16:23.040 --> 16:35.437
And that's kind of the dilemma of a pastor because as a shepherd, sometimes when I see someone that is otherwise minded, the Lord will put on my heart, it's time to talk to them.

16:36.318 --> 16:37.359
Their spirit has changed.

16:37.379 --> 16:39.122
There's a difficulty, there's a problem in their life.

16:39.362 --> 16:40.684
And it's always risk reward.

16:40.724 --> 16:42.386
The reward is, if they say,

16:42.530 --> 16:44.373
Pastor, thanks for caring enough to talk to me.

16:45.656 --> 16:46.257
And you're right.

16:46.377 --> 16:47.579
And I've been having this struggle.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.885
And I just, I go home and I say, praise God, a brother has been one.

16:50.925 --> 16:53.990
The risk is that someone says, get your hands off me.

16:54.010 --> 16:55.173
What are you trying to tell me what to do?

16:57.276 --> 17:00.983
You preachers think you rule the whole world and you're just trying to control my life.

17:03.547 --> 17:05.010
So it's a risk reward thing.

17:06.594 --> 17:16.230
But the last thing that a parent, a pastor, anyone should want to do is to put guilt on someone when there is a far better way of having it dealt with, and that is when God deals with it.

17:17.453 --> 17:18.514
And I want you to remember that.

17:19.596 --> 17:21.099
Real conviction is from the Holy Spirit.

17:21.139 --> 17:27.490
John 16, 7, and 8, the Bible says, when the Holy Spirit comes, he'll reprove the world of sin, of righteousness, and of judgment.

17:27.550 --> 17:30.475
Now, why am I preaching this on the first vision night?

17:30.896 --> 17:32.338
Why would I share this message?

17:33.186 --> 17:37.648
I share it in part because we are ministering in a post-biblical era in America.

17:39.758 --> 17:42.290
We are not in an era

17:43.074 --> 17:52.522
when there are people that are coming into church and there's just this natural momentum or submissiveness or heart of people to say, what do I do next?

17:52.582 --> 17:53.863
And how can I grow in the Lord?

17:53.903 --> 17:54.904
And boy, that was great.

17:54.924 --> 18:02.171
And we are living in an era where people are slower in their trust of authority, much less believing the Bible to be the Word of God.

18:02.511 --> 18:05.654
We're living in an era where people are bringing a tremendous amount of baggage.

18:05.694 --> 18:13.060
And sometimes, and I don't say this to be mean, but their decor and their mannerisms and their vocabulary and their life is very, very

18:13.040 --> 18:16.123
different and sometimes they are otherwise minded.

18:16.183 --> 18:17.144
Could I say it that way?

18:17.385 --> 18:37.006
But the point is that if they're on that path, I spoke about a moment ago and if they're beginning to learn how to worship and they're getting into a community and they're starting into discipleship, what they need at Lancaster Baptist Church is they need a church that will allow God to correct them while we love them to the Lord Jesus Christ.

18:37.026 --> 18:38.888
Now, I'm not speaking about sin.

18:39.188 --> 18:43.012
I'm not speaking about being patient with immorality or being patient with some kind of

18:42.992 --> 18:43.653
open sin.

18:43.874 --> 18:48.802
I'm not advocating to give license to a backsliding Christian and to say, oh, they're off into that.

18:48.862 --> 18:49.684
I guess it's okay.

18:49.944 --> 18:51.988
Go ahead and skip church and party and do all these.

18:52.208 --> 19:04.690
I'm not speaking about that type of a scenario, but I'm speaking about the fact that the fundamental sense of ministry should be this, that there is a God in heaven who can do a better job of changing your husband than you can.

19:06.242 --> 19:09.288
And there's a God in heaven who can help that new Christian.

19:09.648 --> 19:21.350
And if our job perception is that we are here to correct every single person that comes through the door, then we're going to hinder the opportunity that the Holy Spirit can have in changing someone's heart.

19:21.370 --> 19:25.938
And so we want to continually practice individual soul liberty.

19:26.050 --> 19:29.853
We want to recognize that every individual is at a different place.

19:29.893 --> 19:30.754
Now, I've taught that.

19:30.774 --> 19:33.016
It's one of the Baptist's distinctive individual soul liberty.

19:33.036 --> 19:33.677
It's in the Bible.

19:33.737 --> 19:34.417
Daniel 1, 8.

19:34.657 --> 19:39.822
Daniel purposed in his heart that he would not defile himself with a portion of the king's meat.

19:39.842 --> 19:42.604
Now, some of you have raised teenagers and you know what I'm talking about.

